The DevOps market is experiencing significant growth worldwide, fueled by the increasing demand for agile and efficient software development practices. DevOps, which stands for Development and Operations, is a set of practices that combines software development (Dev) and information technology operations (Ops) to reduce the system development life cycle and provide continuous delivery of high-quality software products. The market is driven by the need for faster deployment of applications, improved collaboration between development and operations teams, and automation of manual processes. The global DevOps market is expected to reach a value of $12.85 billion by 2027, with a CAGR of 19.7% during the forecast period of 2020 to 2027.

